Outspan Nigeria Ltd, an Olam Group company has signed a Memorandum of Understanding with the Kano Dairy and Cooperative Union on a pilot milk aggregation and collection model in Kano. The partnership which is under the auspices of the Kano State government and supported by the Federal Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Development, is part of  Olam’s commitment to the growth and development of Nigeria’s Dairy sector. The company said it plans to use the MoU, to develop and execute a backward integration plan that seeks to enhance and support the Dairy Value Chain in line with the federal government’s plan for self-sufficiency in the Dairy industry. A statement from the company made available to LEADERSHIP yesterday, it said through the new partnership, it would be working with Kano Dairy, which is an agglomeration of 74 cooperatives with 12,000 members. According to the statement, Olam plans to set up infrastructure to enable and assist farmers of the Kano Dairy Union to collect, store and transport raw milk in a safe and hygienic environment bringing to bear its experiences garnered from its forays in Russia and Uruguay. The signing of the MoU was witnessed by the permanent secretary Kano State Ministry of Agriculture and Natural resources, Alhaji Adamu Abdu Faragai who represented the deputy governor Kano state as well as the minister of Agriculture and Rural Development, Alhaji Sabo Nanono represented by a director from the Ministry, Alhaji Mohammed Shehu. At the event, head, Olam Dairy, Praveen Paulsamy and chairman Kano Dairy cooperative Union, Alhaji Usman Abdullahi, expressed their happiness in working together to better the lot of Kano Dairy farmers. Outspan Nigeria Ltd which is the Dairy arm of Olam Nigeria limited will also help  facilitate the setting up of Educational initiatives under a Dairy Development Programme (DDP) which will house numerous topics in its curriculum including but not limited to lifecycle management, water management, feed management and artificial insemination. The programme will be run with the objective of ensuring long term sustainable dairy development in the region, improving the livelihood of farmers, reducing dependence on imported raw material and increasing employment opportunities for Kano residents.C